\f0\b \cf2 Secure Element (SE)
\f1\b0 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 An industry-standard chip (Java Card) used for Apple Pay and high-security credentials.\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Connected via a serial interface to the SEP for transaction authorization.\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The "Secure Intent" mechanism relies on a physical link from the side button to the Secure Enclave. When a cryptographic operation requires Secure Intent, the SEP enters a "waiting for confirmation" state. It will only proceed if it receives the hardware interrupt from the side button within a strictly defined time window, typically 60 seconds for Apple Pay transactions. This ensures that no software-only process can simulate the confirmation gesture.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Native iOS Implementation: Security and LocalAuthentication Frameworks\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 The implementation of the confirmatory Face ID flow requires a nuanced understanding of two primary Apple frameworks: \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 LocalAuthentication\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  and \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 Security\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . While many developers believe \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 LAContext\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  is the entry point for all biometric needs, the specific "Confirm with Side Button" behavior for signing operations is often tied to the \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 Security\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  framework\'92s management of Keychain items and Secure Enclave keys.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Distinguishing LAContext from Secure Key Operations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 The \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 LocalAuthentication\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  framework is designed for simple user verification. Using \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 LAContext.evaluatePolicy(.deviceOwnerAuthenticationWithBiometrics)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , an app can check if the user is present. This produces the standard Face ID HUD but does not typically trigger the "Confirm with Side Button" animation unless it is specifically configured in conjunction with Apple Pay or the newer NFC and Secure Element (SE) Platform.\
In contrast, the \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 Security\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  framework allows for the generation of Elliptic Curve (ECC) keys directly within the Secure Enclave. By attaching specific Access Control flags to these keys, an application can mandate that the private key only be used for signing after a successful biometric match and a confirmation of user intent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Specific API Calls and Access Control Flags\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 To achieve a confirmatory flow, the developer must utilize \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 SecAccessControlCreateWithFlags\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . This function defines the conditions under which a keychain item or key can be accessed. The flags provided determine whether the UI will be a simple "look" or a more complex interaction.\

