\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Conclusion and Recommendations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 The "Confirm with Side Button" experience is a specialized implementation of Secure Intent, designed to link physical gestures to cryptographic operations. While the exact UI animation is a system-reserved asset for transaction-heavy contexts like Apple Pay, the underlying security architecture is accessible to third-party developers through the Secure Enclave and the \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 Security\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  framework. By utilizing hardware-bound ECC keys with strict \cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 SecAccessControl\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  flags, the Pakt application can ensure that NDA signatures are only possible when the device owner is physically present and attentive.\
Furthermore, for Pakt to withstand legal scrutiny, the implementation must transition from a simple biometric check to a robust attestation-based system. By storing the ASN.1 DER-encoded signatures and Apple-signed attestation objects, Pakt establishes a non-repudiable evidence chain that proves the identity of the signer and the integrity of the signing device. This combination of hardware-enforced intent and cryptographic proof represents the state of the art in mobile document execution.\
